# ====================== INFO-OPTIONEN ======================
option.info_about=§b§lAbout diesen Shader
option.info_about.comment=§b§lVisual Snow Awareness Shader§r§r for Iris.§r §7Simulates the visual symptoms of VSS — a neurological condition with cortical hyperexcitability. Prevalence ~2.2%. §e[i]§r Goal: awareness, empathy, screening aid.

option.info_default=§a§l▶ How to use this shader
option.info_default.comment=§a§lOverlay model§r §7Each symptom has a master slider (0–100%) — like a layer opacity. §a0%§r = invisible, §c100%§r = full effect. §a1.§r profile button (top left) for quick presets. §a2.§r adjust individual sliders for targeted effects. §a3.§r §6[Advanced]§r buttons open detail parameters per symptom. §a4.§r Master Mix blends the whole effect layer with the original. §c[!]§r Test against detailed terrain, not flat sky — effects dominate uniform surfaces.

option.info_screening=§6§lScreening Guide
option.info_screening.comment=§6§lUsage for parents/pediatricians§r §7Children with congenital VSS often consider their perception normal. §a1.§r Child plays Minecraft normally. §a2.§r Activate §6Screening§r profile (split vertical). §a3.§r Ask: "Does one side look different from the other?" §a4.§r If the child sees no difference or the effect side looks "more normal" — §c[!]§r indication of VSS, consult specialist. §c[!]§r NOT a diagnostic tool.

option.info_static=§b§lAbout Static (Visual Snow)
option.info_static.comment=Core symptom: dynamic granular dots across the entire visual field, > 3 months persistent (ICHD-3, Schankin et al. 2014).

option.info_palinopsia=§b§lAbout Palinopsie
option.info_palinopsia.comment=Afterimages, trailing. Schankin et al. 2020: hypometabolism in the inferior parietal lobule.

option.info_floaters=§b§lAbout Floater
option.info_floaters.comment=Vitreous opacities — perceived with heightened awareness in VSS.

option.info_blue_field=§b§lAbout Blue Field Phenomenon
option.info_blue_field.comment=BFEP: bright dots traveling fast over homogeneous blue surfaces. Caused by white blood cells in retinal capillaries.

option.info_self_light=§b§lAbout Self-light
option.info_self_light.comment=Self-light: colored morphing clouds in deep darkness or with closed eyes.

option.info_photophobia=§b§lAbout Photophobie
option.info_photophobia.comment=Light sensitivity. Eren et al. 2019: in VSS phenomenologically similar to acute migraine.

option.info_nyktalopia=§b§lAbout Nyktalopie
option.info_nyktalopia.comment=Impaired night vision, contrast and saturation loss.

option.info_blue_aggravation=§c§lAbout Blaulicht-Aggravation
option.info_blue_aggravation.comment=§c[!]§r Hepschke et al. 2021: blue cone activation aggravates VSS symptoms.

option.info_disclaimer=§c§l[!] Disclaimer
option.info_disclaimer.comment=§c[!]§r Not a medical diagnostic tool. Echte VSS-Wahrnehmung entsteht im Kortex, nicht auf einem Monitor. Bei Verdacht auf VSS bitte Neuro-Ophthalmologen aufsuchen. ICHD-3 diagnosis requires > 3 months persistent symptoms plus 2 of 4 additional symptoms plus exclusion of other causes.

option.info_credits=§6§lSources & Research
option.info_credits.comment=§6Schankin et al.§r (2014): ICHD-3. §6Puledda, Schankin, Goadsby§r (2020): n=1100. §6Hepschke et al.§r (2021): Blaulicht. §6Eren et al.§r (2019): Photophobie. §6Schankin et al.§r (2020): Palinopsie. §6Martins Silva & Puledda§r (2023). §6Ayesha et al.§r (2025).
